{"id": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/06/10/untitled-5/", "url": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/06/10/untitled-5/", "title": "A major Breakthrough in Oxygen Control for Sparkling Wines", "summary": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1780689121426_061934bb.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"589\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1780689121426_061934bb.png\" width=\"589\" /></p>The LiOX by Diam solution has been designed to meet these requirements, particularly in the case of sparkling wines, where excess oxygen can compromise the aromatic stability and freshness of wines.\" This dialogue with industry stakeholders has resulted in the design of a closure that meets the specific enological requirements of sparkling wines, while incorporating the latest advances in oxygen management.", "content": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1780689121426_061934bb.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"589\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1780689121426_061934bb.png\" width=\"589\" /></p>The LiOX by Diam solution has been designed to meet these requirements, particularly in the case of sparkling wines, where excess oxygen can compromise the aromatic stability and freshness of wines.\" This dialogue with industry stakeholders has resulted in the design of a closure that meets the specific enological requirements of sparkling wines, while incorporating the latest advances in oxygen management.", "published_at": "2026-0