{"id": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/06/10/untitled-5/", "url": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/06/10/untitled-5/", "title": "A major Breakthrough in Oxygen Control for Sparkling Wines", "summary": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1780689121426_061934bb.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"589\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1780689121426_061934bb.png\" width=\"589\" /></p>The LiOX by Diam solution has been designed to meet these requirements, particularly in the case of sparkling wines, where excess oxygen can compromise the aromatic stability and freshness of wines.\" This dialogue with industry stakeholders has resulted in the design of a closure that meets the specific enological requirements of sparkling wines, while incorporating the latest advances in oxygen management.", "content": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1780689121426_061934bb.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"589\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1780689121426_061934bb.png\" width=\"589\" /></p>The LiOX by Diam solution has been designed to meet these requirements, particularly in the case of sparkling wines, where excess oxygen can compromise the aromatic stability and freshness of wines.\" This dialogue with industry stakeholders has resulted in the design of a closure that meets the specific enological requirements of sparkling wines, while incorporating the latest advances in oxygen management.", "published_at": "2026-06-10 23:06:07+00:00", "source_name": "Wine Industry Advisor", "source_type": "media", "language": "en", "content_type": "market_report", "country": "US", "continent": "NEW_WORLD", "region": "Americas/North/USA", "producer_role": "trade_media", "trust_tier": "T3_professional", "info_purpose": ["P2_market_analysis"], "collection_tier": "C1_rss"}
{"id": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/06/10/untitled-4/", "url": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/06/10/untitled-4/", "title": "Tariff Refund Opportunity for Wineries", "summary": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"258\" src=\"https://win-advisor-media-library.s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/18014545/Brotemarkle-Davis-Co.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"320\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"258\" src=\"https://win-advisor-media-library.s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/18014545/Brotemarkle-Davis-Co.jpg\" width=\"320\" /></p>If you purchased these items through a U.S. distributor, the importer of record would typically be the distributor. This change in policy creates a potential opportunity for wineries that imported certain goods directly during the affected period.", "content": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"258\" src=\"https://win-advisor-media-library.s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/18014545/Brotemarkle-Davis-Co.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"320\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"258\" src=\"https://win-advisor-media-library.s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/18014545/Brotemarkle-Davis-Co.jpg\" width=\"320\" /></p>If you purchased these items through a U.S. distributor, the importer of record would typically be the distributor. This change in policy creates a potential opportunity for wineries that imported certain goods directly during the affected period.", "published_at": "2026-06-10 23:05:13+00:00", "source_name": "Wine Industry Advisor", "source_type": "media", "language": "en", "content_type": "market_report", "country": "US", "continent": "NEW_WORLD", "region": "Americas/North/USA", "producer_role": "trade_media", "trust_tier": "T3_professional", "info_purpose": ["P2_market_analysis"], "collection_tier": "C1_rss"}
{"id": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/06/10/untitled-3/", "url": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/06/10/untitled-3/", "title": "Warehouse Technologies That Improve Safety, Visibility, and Productivity", "summary": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"303\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1781105693991_592cdafc.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"640\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"484\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1781105693991_592cdafc.png\" width=\"1024\" /></p>At Papé Material Handling, we help businesses across the West evaluate technology as part of a larger warehouse strategy that includes equipment, fleet tools, automation, layout planning, and power solutions. On a practical level, these tools can help reduce damage to equipment and products, promote employee safety and compliance, lower costs through wireless management, improve fuel consumption, and keep maintenance and repair needs more visible.", "content": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"303\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1781105693991_592cdafc.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"640\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"484\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/1781105693991_592cdafc.png\" width=\"1024\" /></p>At Papé Material Handling, we help businesses across the West evaluate technology as part of a larger warehouse strategy that includes equipment, fleet tools, automation, layout planning, and power solutions. On a practical level, these tools can help reduce damage to equipment and products, promote employee safety and compliance, lower costs through wireless management, improve fuel consumption, and keep maintenance and repair needs more visible.", "published_at": "2026-06-10 23:05:06+00:00", "source_name": "Wine Industry Advisor", "source_type": "media", "language": "en", "content_type": "market_report", "country": "US", "continent": "NEW_WORLD", "region": "Americas/North/USA", "producer_role": "trade_media", "trust_tier": "T3_professional", "info_purpose": ["P2_market_analysis"], "collection_tier": "C1_rss"}
